  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>MAD Mount Hotel is offered on bed and breakfast. </p>
<p>Breakfast consists of continental buffet served between 7am - 10am.</p>
<p>In the hotel's on-site restaurant an a la carte dinner menu is available each evening. The hotel <span>offers a variety of dishes inspired by Italian cuisine and other flavours from around the world - Pizzas, Japanese Tuna tataki, and Swiss grilled cheese among others, are on the menu too, combined with local beers and wines. Vegetarian options are also available.</span></p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>Located just steps away from the <span>Nendaz telecabine, this hotel is in a central location in Nendaz, giving you easy access to all the resort amenities and the 4 Valleys ski area. Built in a modern style with cabin style accommodation it is a fantastic choice for your next Swiss ski holiday. </span></p>
<h2>Restaurant and bar</h2>
<p>The hotel has its own restaurant where you'll have an a la carte dinner. You'll have the opportunity to try a variety of different foods. On the menu you'll find dishes inspired by Italian cuisine, Japanese cuisine and traditional Swiss delicacies. </p>
<p>The terrace bar allows you to appreciate the outdoors from the warmth of the inside. The large open windows give panoramic views of the surrounding mountains which are the perfect backdrop for an evening filled with local cocktails and wine. Plus after a day on the slopes you can enjoy a drink outside and admire the views of the surrounding mountain peaks with a cocktail or local beer. </p>
<h2>Luxury spa </h2>
<p>Despite its small and cosy size, the MAD Mount offers you a range of spa facilities included during your stay. The hotels luxury spa area has 7 wellness amenities for you to use to unwind after an energetic day out on the mountain. Make the most of the hammam and tropical sauna or relax not just your body but your mind too in the Japanese Onsen - a natural hot spring.</p>
<h2>Sustainability MAD</h2>
<p>Throughout the hotel, you'll find various notes to the great outdoors. All of the bedrooms are built in a cabin-inspired design, using locally sourced wood from Swiss forests and natural materials - even the floors are made from 98% organic and recyclable materials! During your stay, you'll also benefit from the hotel's natural insulation, so not only will you be getting warm and toasty in the comforts of a log cabin bedroom, but you'll also feel great doing it. </p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
